Indian Stocks Snaps Eight-Day Rally; Climbs for the Second Week

-- B y   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 
2011-04-01T10:11:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/indian-stocks-snaps-eight-day-rally-climbs-for-the-second-week.html
India ’s benchmark stock index fell,
ending an eight-day rally, on concern higher energy prices will
fan inflation.  State Bank of India (SBIN) , the nation’s biggest lender, paced
declines among its peers. Oil reached a 30-month high in  New
York  on concern the conflict in  Libya ,  Africa ’s third-largest
exporter, will prolong production cuts and spread to Middle East
producers.  Maruti Suzuki India Ltd. (MSIL) , the top carmaker, rose to a
one-month high after sales rose to a record in March. Foreign
funds were net buyers shares for a seventh day.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, fell
19.34, or 0.1 percent, to 19,425.88, according to preliminary
closing prices at 3:30 p.m. in Mumbai. The gauge, which swung
between gains and losses at least 20 times, advanced for a
second week. The S&P CNX Nifty Index on the National Stock
Exchange dropped 0.1 percent to 5,828.05, while its April
futures settled at 5,865. The BSE 200 Index gained 0.3 percent
to 2,385.87.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rajhkumar K Shaaw in Mumbai at 
